==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Utensil
<hw>U*ten"sil</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>utensile</ets>, <ets>ustensile</ets>, L. <ets>utensile</ets>, fr.
<ets>utensilis</ets> that may be used, fit for use, fr. <ets>uti</ets>,
p. p. <ets>usus</ets>, to use. See <er>Use</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<def>That which is used; an instrument; an implement; especially, an
instrument or vessel used in a kitchen, or in domestic and farming
business.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wagons fraught with <qex>utensils</qex> of war.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uterine</ent>⟦br⟧
